description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a band 3 physiotherapy assistant to join our ward team at Springwood in Malton which is a 14 bedded complex needs unit for older people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of paid or voluntary work with people with mental health conditions is essential. Experience of working to support the work of a Physiotherapist would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must demonstrate good verbal and written skills, be honest and trustworthy and be able to work independently on delegated tasks under the direction of qualified staff as well as under direct supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will benefit from being part of a group of 60 Physiotherapy staff working in TEWV, 30 of whom work in mental health services for older people, with guidance from Clinical Leads, Clinical Specialists and the Professional Head of Physiotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work independently on the ward as well as alongside a qualified physiotherapist and as part of the wider multi-disciplinary team on the ward. You must have a relevant NVQ Level 3 in care or equivalent or a willingness to undertake it within an agreed timescale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional attractive features of this post includes flexible working, a robust clinical supervision scheme, an excellent training &amp; development programme, and supportive professional leadership from the Professional Head of Physiotherapy. We are also committed to supporting external training events, CPD, research and audit interests under our appraisal scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Waines, Clinical Lead Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;amanda.waines@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07384249023&lt;/p&gt;
